        body: '## Description  \r\nI\'m handling the `onCellEdit` event and I want to commit my transaction to my backend service. \r\nThe `onRowEdit` and `onCellEdit` events are documented as events that fire after editing is committed, which is simply not true, since both events are cancellable. There\'s currently no events that can be subscribed to, which fire after editing has been committed.\r\n\r\n> Note: Initially this issue was also describing the problems below, however they were resolved by #4965 \r\n> - I cannot extract from the event which column the edit was performed for.\r\n> - Also, the event args have no `owner` and I cannot extract the grid context.\r\n> - Also, if hiding is performed, the column index is wrong, and the correct column cannot be retrieved.\r\n\r\n * igniteui-angular version: 9.0.13\r\n * browser: N/A\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce  \r\n\r\n1. Define a grid\r\n2. Define editing for cells in it\r\n3. Handle `onCellEdit` and inspect the event arguments\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<igx-grid [data]="orders" [height]="\'300px\'" primaryKey="id" (onCellEdit)="editDone($event)" [cellSelection]="\'none\'">\r\n  <igx-column field="confirmed" [dataType]="\'boolean\'" [editable]="true" header="">\r\n  </igx-column>\r\n  <igx-column field="shipped" [dataType]="\'boolean\'" [editable]="true" header="">\r\n  </igx-column>\r\n</igx-grid>\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Result  \r\n`console.log(args)` gives me this:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1472513/81573695-7e8cbf80-93ad-11ea-9c95-55bbb956835a.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n## Expected result  \r\nI want editing events after edits are committed (as documented).\r\n\r\n\r\n## Attachments  \r\nAttach a sample if available, and screenshots, if applicable.  \r\n\r\n',
